[mysqli_fetch_row](https://www.php.net/manual/en/mysqli-result.fetch-row.php) fetches &quot;one row of data from the result set and returns it as an enumerated array, where each column is stored in an array offset starting from 0 (zero).&quot; So the key of the column is the same as column order.

So you can do this:

```php
while($row = mysqli_fetch_row($sql)) {
    echo &#39;&lt;tr&gt;&#39;; 
    foreach ($row as $key =&gt; $col) {
        if ($key === 0) {
          echo &quot;&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href = &#39;https://whatismyipaddress.com/ip-lookup&#39; target = &#39;_blank&#39;&gt;$col&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&quot;;
        }
    }
    echo &#39;&lt;/tr&gt;&#39;;
}
```

But column is subjected to changes in database structure and SQL query changes. I would personally prefer [mysqli_fetch_assoc](https://www.php.net/manual/en/mysqli-result.fetch-assoc.php) or [mysqli_fetch_object](https://www.php.net/manual/en/mysqli-result.fetch-object.php) so I can use the column by name instead of order number. Its less error prone. For example,

```php
while($row = mysqli_fetch_assoc($sql)) {
    echo &#39;&lt;tr&gt;&#39;; 
    foreach ($row as $key =&gt; $col) {
        if ($key === &#39;ip_address&#39;) {
          echo &quot;&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href = &#39;https://whatismyipaddress.com/ip-lookup&#39; target = &#39;_blank&#39;&gt;$col&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&quot;;
        }
    }
    echo &#39;&lt;/tr&gt;&#39;;
}
```

Note: `$sql` here should be a `mysqli_query` result instead of the actual SQL string.

**Type:1** you may use `array_key_first`

    foreach($row as $key =&gt; $value){
        if ($key === array_key_first($row)){
        echo &#39;FIRST ELEMENT!&#39;;
        }  
    }

**Type:2** you may use the key as well.

    foreach($row as $key =&gt; $value){
        if ($key === 0){
        echo &#39;FIRST ELEMENT!&#39;;
        }  
    }

**Type: 3** The first time you&#39;ll get true then it&#39;ll be false.

    $first = true; 
    foreach ($row as $key =&gt; $value)
    {
      if ( $first )
      {
        // do something
        $first = false; //in order not to get into the if statement for the next loops
      }
      else
      {
        // do something else for all loops except the first
      }
    }

